revision.text: Possibly: The new and complete dictionary of the German and English languages composed chiefly after the German Dictionaries of Mr. Adelung and of Mr. Schwan. Every German Word being rendered into proper English and thoroughly enriched with Phrases and Terms of Arts and Sciences: A Work, which will be useful and even indispensible, and therefore welcome to all such as have a Mind to translate or read the Works of either of the two Languages, elaborated by John Ebers. 3v. (Leipzig : Printed for Breitkopf and Haertel, 1796-1799). http://library.st-andrews.ac.uk/record=b2489100~S1
